description:
Death of a Nation

The world is in peril. Empress Pineapple uses a recent terrorist attack in the Grand Dessert (yes dessert; like cake and ice cream) to expand the Garden Empire across the Birdlands and colonize its inhabitants; the humble Fish People. Representative Chip of the Mousse Coalition, commissions Col. Bird of the Mousse Intelligence Foods to investigate industrialist Dairy Cheesewheel Cheddarfeller's possible financing of the attack. What MIF agents Black Ham and Hot Dog discover is a conspiracy that will result in the greatest financial and military crisis the tasty Mousse Coalition has ever faced. Cola help us all. Also, all the characters are food items.
name: Death of a Nation

description:
Better known for explorations of childhood friendship (Yikes!) and life in pre-apocalyptic America (Barack Hussein Obama), Butter and Blood showcases Steven Weissman's wider, weirder range as a cartoonist.

Butter and Blood collects work created for patrons as varied as Giant Robot, Vice, Mome, Playboy, The Stranger and Nickelodeon, as well as sticker designs, sketchbook pages and much more.

Featuring roving gangs of drug-addled rabbits, Guns N' Roses in their Jewish deli days, ghost stories and talking dogs with nothing to say, Butter and Blood is packed cover-to-cover with beautiful drawing, dumb ideas and funny, funny jokes.

Prelude

Butterfly is the killer comic book prelude to the Deep Penitentiary 6 novella. When Theta Butterfly crosses paths with a former cult associate she is seduced by sweet revenge and sets out to murder the man that made her, Dr. Purple.
name: Prelude

description: Kerry Passan and her crew Impact Terra plan on taking over the Delta from three other factions. The first step they take is to pay a visit to The Brevary brothers - a pair of swamp gunrunners - but this only leads to... "complications".

What was supposed to be simple heist gets complicated for Nate Avery and his crew of rogues, especially when they find out the cargo is not what it appears.

On the run from the corporate entity known as "The Fountain" who will stop at nothing to get their hands on it, and the arrival of a mysterious man of great power, the stakes have never been higher and so they are forced to hide out in a place that only thieves, opportunists and assassins dare to call home.

The Outlands.

Battle One

In the future, the entertainment industry has suffered so much that the only method is live gladiatorial battles to the death, with super powered fighters. A boy named Dae is captured and sold to an eight-year-old girl Mia who is still naive about what she's truly asking her new and only friend to do.
name: Battle 1

description: From the castles of medieval England to the unstoppable armies of Genghis Khan, these 25 tales of zombie-stabbing action traverse the histories of the ancient world before the machinery of modern combat was perfected. These were brutal times when you either LIVED by the sword or DIED by the horde!

volume.name: FUBAR: By the Sword: Expanded Edition

description:
Mia the Lynx

Mia is a lynx with a secret girlfriend that her parents and other lynxes must never find out about. All her life Mia has been taught that lynxes can't be friends with other animals, until she falls in love with a wolf! What happens when Mia and her girlfriend get caught by Mia's controlling parents? Can the lynx and the wolf girl ever be together?

Mia the Lynx is a romantic drama about a forbidden love, facing up to prejudice and making a difficult life decision.
name: Mia the Lynx

description:
Drayven

Discover the true origin of the Vampire.

This 3000 year old love triangle begins in the ancient city of Babylon, then continues to modern day Chicago. There is a millenia old battle between good and evil. The Nephilim of Ancient Days must flee from the curses of Moses. These demonic beings must seek new refuge within the souls of mankind. But when one temptress goes too far, she unleashes a power that may destroy the legendary creatures forever.
name: Drayven

description:
Fighting is my Monday

Remember when you were a kid and you thought you were going to be a rock star?

Arena shows. Champagne. Thousands of people chanting your name... your life was going to be one long limo ride. Then you wake up one day and you're 30 and the limo never came. It's like that only I never wanted to be a rock star...

I wanted to take over the world...

Amateur bad guy, Trevor Werner, the sinister Mister Twist enters an uneasy alliance with two fellow criminal also-rans: bruised, beautiful Olive Armstrong and aging 60's super-radical, Agent Orange when the trio stumble upon the passed out body of a left-for-dead superhero. The plan is simple: ransom the hero at an underworld 'black auction' and split the take three ways. Of course, like all simple plans it goes murderously awry...
name: Fighting Is My Monday

description: Ignatz Award nominee Yumi Sakugawa (I Think I Am In Friend-Love With You) presents a powerful exploration of a piece of performance art. Cassie Hamasaki embodies a Japanese flower arrangement, and then, trailing her confused art class, she silently walks into the city, through a public utterly unaware of what she is doing.

In a Small Town

Having not seen each other in many years, Nathan Jones reconnects with the members of the all-female Junk Rock band Pitch Girl when they play a show in New York city. Before they drifted apart Nathan was close friends with the members or Pitch Girl, especially lead singer Bianca Kovacks. It has always been Bianca's burning desire to escape the doldrums of growing up in go-nowhere, suburban college town. She formed Pitch Girl for specifically this purpose. But on the cusp of hitting the road for Pitch Girl's first tour, Bianca is having doubts about not only leaving her comfort zone, but leaving her best friend behind too.
name: In A Small Town

description:
"The Magic is Alive!" Collects Champions (1987 Heroic) #9, Flare (1988 1st Series) #2, Flare (1989 2nd Series) #1, 3, and 5, and Lady Arcane (1992) #1.

Written by Dennis Mallonee and Colin Wales. Art by Chris Marrinan, Dell Barras, Howard Simpson, and Duval Stowers. Cover by Duval Stowers. Begin the Quest for Lady Arcane with this trade paperback collection of her classic early adventures! These are Donnah Victoria Hannah's most sought-after tales, featuring guest appearances by Flare, Doctor Arcane, and the ever-naughty Black Enchantress!
name: Book One

volume.name: Lady Arcane: The Magic is Alive

description: Set in a future where Earth no longer exists, we meet a young mage named Toran. Toran has finally come of age, and being one of the only three mages in his town he is understandably nervous for his tests today. In a world full of magic and technology Toran lives on the distant northern slopes of a backwater world. Today visitors from the ruling race have come to judge the strength of will Toran and his college possess, if they fail it means their lives. But before the tests can even begin chaos strikes! Monsters known only as the Tainted are captured and caged inside the town, a woman known to exist only in myth joins them in the stone cells, and just as the sun sets and Toran steps up to bat violent blue light fills the air as dark horrors rain down around them. Toran is left in chaos fighting for his life. What is going on? How can he stop it? Does this mean he's failed his tests???

Angelino is a young loser like thousands of others in the Dark Meat City. He and his friend Vinz are squatters at a seedy hotel room in the Latin Quarter, Rios Rosas. Angelino spends his days watching Mexican wrestling matches on TV, delivering pizzas and having bizarre metaphysical discussions with his roommate. A stupid scooter accident will plunge Angelino into a hurricane of unimaginable trouble, as he becomes the only person on Earth capable of recognizing the vicious cosmic entities that walk among us, who are readying themselves to invade the planet.

Note: The digital edition (9/23/2015) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Dark Meat City

description:
Detective Satoshi Yamada has just been handed one of the strangest cases of his career. A young high school student is murdered, and the only clue is a mysterious tattoo of the Black Lotus.

As the trail of the killer leads him from high school, into the depths of high society, Yamada must confront a secret from his past better left buried. A secret Sundiata must unearth!

OswaldDoingThings” is a silent, macabre yet comical series of short stories that follows a round-headed, clumsy and very unlucky character named Oswald.

It’s dark, gore, yet quite endearing.

The tragedy of Oswald’s perpetual demise is alleviated by the fact that he makes a comeback every single time… to die all over again, to the reader’s utmost satisfaction.

(“OswaldDoingThings” Volume 1 includes the first 100 short stories of the on-going title.)
In order to overcome insomnia, Ninel has started sleeping in an isolation tank. But now she's having dreams about a large, ancient, undersea creature of some sort. They're just dreams though, right?

The story of a man with no memory and a deadly past trying to catch him at every turn. A gritty western inspired mystery that will leave you gut wrenched. Return to Rander: The Lone Savior contains the first four issues of the Return to Rander comic book series as well as loads of bonus content. This is the first step to finding where Rander is!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Return To Rander: The Lone Savior

description:
Meet William Wade, Civil War vet, reluctant secret agent answering to President Rutherford B. Hayes, and zombie-hunter!

In "Reactivated," Agent Wade begins his mission with partner J.J. Flynn in a mining town locked down in a labor dispute and a siege of the undead.

Plus, the two agents go undercover in an isolated, snowbound, debauched Army fort under slow attack by the undead-uncovering a Donner-like party and the fact that the wretched things are arising in different species everywhere.

Collecting the first six issues of the acclaimed zombie-Western epic with an edgy topical bite.
name: Volume One

description:
GEEKY FERTILITY RESEARCHER PETER COTTON IS BITTEN BY A MUTANT RABBIT AND CHANGES INTO THE HALF-MAN/HALF-BUNNY ROTTENTAIL.

WHAT'S A BOY TO DO?

WHY, TAKE A HIPPITY, HOPPITY TRIP HOME OF COURSE!

PETER BEGINS A BLOODY KILLING SPREE OF REVENGE THAT CULMINATES IN HIS CHILDHOOD HOMETOWN OF EASTER FALLS.

When Peter gets a new gig as a night watchmen, his only warning is to stay out of the warehouse. As you might imagine, he ignores that warning and discovers just what happens to the mannequins when the full moon is out!
More humor and anger from late night TV comedy writer Jose Arroyo. Check out the cheap online copy price!

Richard is having a very bad week. His fiancée dumped him. His friends are losing their minds. And his job truly sucks.

As Phantasm, Richard is the sidekick to Mr. Marvelous -- Chicago's most beloved superhero. Unfortunately, Mr. Marvelous also sports Chicago's most inflated ego, endlessly reminding Richard of the realities of the "hero/sidekick" dynamic: Mr. Marvelous is to be worshipped... while Phantasm is to remain a bit player. Cleaning up the mess. Or risk being replaced.

Along with his colleagues -- Mustang, Jolt, Atlas, and Frostbite -- Richard is beginning to realize that not only are his ilk disrespected by the heroes they work with, but they're ignored by the media and taken for granted by society, as well.

How much can these five sidekicks endure before they decide they've had enough? And then what???

Sleepy Hollow - The Show Companion brings together the best of Sleepy Hollow Magazine, along with brand new material! Inside you'll find exclusive interviews with Sleepy Hollow's stars Tom Mison and Nicole Beharie, as well as with some of the actors who play Ichabod and Abbie's trusted friends and terrifying foes, including Katia Winter, Lyndie Greenwood, John Noble, Neil Jackson and Matt Barr.

This book contains Squirrels 1 and 2. Squirrels 1: Why do we see so many squirrels as roadkill? This story may answer your questions. Squirrels 2: What happened to the White Squirrel of Trinity Bellwoods Park and why was he found hanging by his teeth from a powerline?
This "sweets" themed zine contains comics, illustrations, and recipes, by 24 different artists.

Long before being part of the quest to retrieve the stolen Great Seal of Iberion, Gabriel was a young music student dreaming of entertaining the courts of the realm. Instead, he found himself captured in a barbarian raid and forced to train not in the music he loves but instead in war and brutality.

Escaping his captors, Gabriel starts a new life only to find that threatened by the barbarians that chase him, but this time he has the help of a Kreston Knight with an enchanted blade...

volume.name: Tall Tails: Or So I Thought

description:
Graduation Day!

Only one test left for these special heroes: To graduate, they have to die!
name: Graduation Day!

description: The Women of Marvel are taking over in September! That's right, Marvel's blockbuster female-led titles are returning to comic shops this month for ten new TRUE BELIEVERS titles. Specially priced at $1, these can't miss introductory issues provide the perfect window into some of Marvel's critically acclaimed female-led titles! From the high stakes espionage action of Black Widow to the out of this world adventure of Princess Leia. From the larger than life Ms. Marvel to the irresistible charm of Spider-Gwen - these fan-favorite premiere issues offer perfect entry points into the Marvel Universe. Hang on tight and see what you've been missing with these exciting TRUE BELIEVERS titles coming to comic shops in September!

Collects Women of Gold Digger, Women of Gold Digger Spring Break, and Women of Gold Digger Summer Vacation Special.

A.P. presents a captivating collection of informative and entertaining glimpses at Fred Perry's mighty misses and Mrs. of Gold Digger. Even with three full issues' worth of profile pages and short stories, this terrific trade features but a fraction of that comely cast, but with so many strong subjects, they need their space to shine! See why Gold Digger has the most engaging, strong, and inspiring female characters in the world!
name: TPB

description: Imagine a world at war. A place where you had to fight; you had to kill or be killed. Imagine waking up one morning to find out you were part of this war, you had no choice.

What the Hell is Log Fu?

After years of hard work Big Red McLane has finally saved Pacific City. Nobody's trying to steal the First International Bank or poison the water supply...

But out in the North Woods an epic plan is taking shape. All of Red's old enemies are coming together. And soon a question that has stood unanswered for a quarter century will finally be decided: Who is the World's Greatest Lumberjack?
name: What the Hell is Log Fu?

description: With art by over 30 of Carnals best artists. A behind the scenes look at the history of one of the longest running x-rated comic publishers in the biz! Full of unpublished Carnal & Demi art, pages of never-before-seen photos of porn stars Jill Kelly, Christi Lake, Annabel Chong, Minka, Sarah Jane-Hamilton & others. A complete history of Carnal, including the unsolved murder of Carnals 1st publisher, Todd Loren. A must - have book for anyone interested in adult comics or the porno industry. 56 pages

volume.name: Carnal Comics: The inside Story of Art, Sex, & Porn Stars
True Stories of Adult Film Stars: Jenna Jameson

description: Determined to reckon once and for all with one of his fiercest adversaries, the main responsible of the tragical end of his beloved Lisa, Harlan enlists the help of his friends Mulawa, Ann Jurging and Caleb Lost, as well as recruiting two “fellow countrymen” of Thorke, Khaled and Ryakar. Their well-conceived trap will entice Thorke to Prague, where Caleb can confront and destroy the demon through the power of the Light. But apparently something goes wrong and the Flesh-eating Demon overcomes the magical fortification created by Caleb and Ann, penetrates into the theater and jumps on the defenseless girl, Ljiuba...
name: La Furia di Thorke

person_credits.name: Michel Fiffe
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Zits Guide to Living with Your Teenager

name: Danger in the Streets! ; The Endless Journey

description: At the end of Impasse Chaptal, a colorful alley in Paris, there’s the building that once was home to the famous “thrill theater”, the Grand Guignol. The passionate collector and lover of thespian memorabilia, Monsieur Mathis, is trying to bring the theater back to its old splendor, but the savvy modern audiences just laugh at his revival of old classics in the “terror” genre. An outraged Mathis accepts the co-coperation of a mysterious character, the self-appointed Prince Sho Huan, who tells Mathis that he aims to bring back real blood and true fear onto the stage... The dark producer keeps his promise, in a crescendo of crimes and madness that will involve Harlan and his Parisian friend, Angélique, in a revival of old enemies on the boards of that ghostly stage...
name: Serata al Grand Guignol

volume.name: Roy Rogers e o Trigger: Suplemento ao Mundo de Aventuras

deck: Tarzan Adventures was a British weekly series that consisted of reprinted comics strips, original stories and text pieces.
